Samsung’s dual screen device, the 7 Pro, launched late last year. The larger of the two, it’s more impressively gorgeous than the 6.3-inch Infinity, which debuted alongside the Galaxy S10 in 2016.

The 7 Pro will be Samsung’s second-generation phone, following the [Galaxy S10](&lt;|url|&gt;). The larger also better meets [the company’s new guidelines](&lt;|url|&gt;) for choosing AMOLED screens.

![](<|image|>)

There’s also the oddity of needing two screens to run the 7 Pro. One is used for social media, but the other doubles as a new revenue-sharing program for Samsung. There’s no doubt the company could make this a co-brand, but as of yet, there’s no indication it’s willing to give away anything substantial for the foreseeable future.

